<item>
            <title>[LU-11064] o2iblnd fast reg gaps case is determined incompletely </title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11064</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;We&apos;re allowed to start at a non-aligned page offset in the first fragment and end at a non-aligned page offset in the last fragment.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently the first fragment is not considered. So it&apos;s possible to start on a non-aligned page boundary and consider that there is a gap in the transmit buffer, which is not correct.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="52435">LU-11064</key>
            <summary>o2iblnd fast reg gaps case is determined incompletely </summary>
